# Movie Finder Chain — Cursor Rules

You are working in the movie-finder-chain workspace.
Primary reference: CLAUDE.md (loaded automatically; also valid for Cursor).

## What this workspace does

LangGraph 8-node AI pipeline.
classify → search_rag → enrich_imdb → reason → route → refine / confirm / answer

## All quality commands run inside Docker

```bash
make lint            # ruff check
make typecheck       # mypy --strict
make test            # pytest tests/
make test-coverage   # pytest + reports/
make pre-commit      # full hook suite
```

## Critical rules

- State machine: new behaviour = new node or edge, NEVER branching inside existing nodes
- Nodes are pure functions: take MovieFinderState, return partial state update
- Access MovieFinderState fields with .get() and safe defaults (issue #15 — total=False)
- Never re-create OpenAI/Qdrant clients inside nodes (issue #7)
- Node construction is centralised in graph.py — no wiring elsewhere
- Configuration: Pydantic BaseSettings in config.py — never os.getenv() in nodes
- Models: Claude Haiku for classify nodes, Claude Sonnet for reason/Q&A nodes

## Python rules

- mypy --strict on all node functions
- No print() — LangSmith handles observability
- Line length: 100

## IMDb enrichment rules

- Sequential (no concurrent semaphore) — Cloudflare rate-limits concurrent requests
- Respect retry_after from HTTP 429 response body
- Max candidates before enrichment: _MAX_ENRICH_CANDIDATES = 5
